Copa Libertadores de América 1960 - Details

Overview Page| 1960 (overview)

About this document

Teams: Peñarol (Uruguay), Millonarios (Colombia), Olimpia (Paraguay), San Lorenzo (Argentina), Esporte Clube Bahia (Brasil), Jorge Wilstermann (Bolivia), Universidad de Chile (Chile). The champion national teams of Ecuador, Peru and Venezuela did not participate in the first edition.
 

First Round

Group A (Argentina, Brasil)

20.04.1960 - San Lorenzo (Arg) 3 - EC Bahia (Bra) 0

San Lorenzo : Vladimir Tarnawski, Paez, Iñigo, Castillo, Reynoso, Ravecca, Hector Facundo (Carlos Salvador Bilardo), Ruiz, Oscar Rossi, José Francisco Sanfilippo, Norberto Boggio.
EC Bahia : Nadinho, Leone, Henrique Santos, Beto, Flavio Santos, Vicente Arenale Filho, Marito, Aléncar, Leo, Ari, Biriba.
Goals: Rossi (SL), Ruiz (SL), Sanfilippo (SL).
Sent off: Vicente Arenale Filho (ECB)
Stadium: Huracan (Buenos Aires)
Referee: Esteban Marino (Uruguay)
Attedance: 10.000

03.05.1960 - EC Bahia (Bra) 3 - San Lorenzo (Arg) 2

EC Bahia: Nadinho, Leone, Henrique Santos, Beto, Flavio Santos, Nelzinho, Marito, Leo, Carlitos, Mario, Biriba.
San Lorenzo : Vladimir Tarnawski, Cancino, Iñigo, Castillo, Reynoso, Ravecca, Hector Facundo (Benitez), Ruiz, Oscar Rossi, José Francisco Sanfilippo, Norberto Boggio.
Goals : Carlitos (ECB), Flavio (ECB), Marito (ECB), Sanfilippo -2- (SL)
Stadium : Fonte Nova (Bahia)
Referee : Eustasio Catebeke (Paraguay)
Attendance : 18.000

Qualified : San Lorenzo (Argentina)

 

Group B (Uruguay, Bolivia)

19.04.1960 - Peñarol (Uru) 7 - Jorge Wilstermann (Bol) 1

Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Nestor Goncálvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Luis Eduardo Hohberg, Alberto Pedro Spencer, Borges.
Jorge Wilstermann : Rico, Claure, Villaroel, Trujillo, Rocabado, Zabalaga, Sánchez, M. Alcólcer, A. Garcia, R. Lopez, Cortez (Soria).
Goals : Spencer -4- (P), Borges -2- (P), Luis Cubilla (P), M. Alcólcer (JW).
Stadium : Centenario (Montivedeo)
Referee : Carlos Robles (Chile)
Attendance : 35.000

30.04.1960 - Jorge Wilstermann (Bol) 1 - Peñarol (Uru) 1

Jorge Wilstermann : Zamorano, Vargas, Trujillo, Claure, Rocabado, Zabalaga, Soria, M. Alcólcer, A. Garcia, R. Lopez, Cortez.
Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Nestor Goncálvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Alberto Spencer (Leicht), Pedra, Borges.
Goals : Garcia (JW), Luis Cubilla (P).
Stadium : Hernando Siles (La Paz)
Referee : José Luis Praddaude (Argentina)
Attendance : 30.000

Qualified : Peñarol (Uruguay)

 

Group C (Chile, Colombia)

08.05.1960 - Universidad de Chile (Chi) 0 - Millonarios (Col) 6

Universidad de Chile : Pacheco, Eyzaguirre, Donoso, Navarro, Contreras, Sepúlveda, Musso, Alvarez, Campos, Leonel Sanchez, O. Diaz (Ibarra).
Millonarios : Centurion, Moyano, Bolla, Zuluaga, J. Ramirez Gallego, R. Diaz, Orlando Larraz, Rodolfo Micheli, R. J. Castro (Alarcón), Klinger, R. Pizarro.
Goals : Klinger -2- (M), Pizarro -2- (M), Micheli (M), Larraz (M).
Stadium : Nacional (Santiago)
Referee : Juan Carlos Armental (Uruguay)
Attendance : 18.000

15.05.1960 - Millonarios (Col) 1 - Universidad de Chile (Chi) 0

Millonarios : Centurion, Moyano, Bolla, Zuluaga, J. Ramirez Gallego, R. Diaz, Orlando Larraz, Rodolfo Micheli, Alarcon (R. J. Castro), Klinger, R. Pizarro.
Universidad de Chile : Astorga, Eyzaguirre, Villanueva, Navarro, Contreras, Sepulveda, O. Diaz, Alvarez, Campos, Leonel Sanchez, Ibarra (Musso).
Goals : Micheli (M).
Stadium : Nemesio Camacho, "El Campin" (Bogota)
Referee : Juan Carlos Armental (Uruguay)
Attendance : 25.000

Qualified : Millonarios (Colombia)

Olimpia (Paraguay) bye.

 

Semifinals

18.05.1960 - Peñarol (Uru) 1 - San Lorenzo (Arg) 1

Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Nestor Goncalvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Juan Eduardo Hohberg, Spencer, Borges.
San Lorenzo : Tarnawski (Carrillo), Cancino, Iñigo, Castillo, Reynoso, Ravecca, Facundo, Ruiz, Oscar Rossi, Sanfilippo (Carlos Bilardo), Boggio.
Goals : Linazza (P), Boggio (SL).
Stadium : Centenario (Montevideo)
Referee : Carlos Robles (Chile)
Attendance : 55.000
Sent-off : Iñigo (SL)

24.05.1960 -  San Lorenzo (Arg) 0 - Peñarol (Uru) 0

San Lorenzo : Tarnawski, Cancino, Paez, Castillo, Reynoso, Ferro, Facundo (Carlos Bilardo), Ruiz, Oscar Rossi, Sanfilippo, Boggio.
Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Goncalvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Spencer, Griecco, Leicht.
Stadium : Huracan (Buenos Aires)
Referee : Carlos Robles (Chile)
Attendance : 15.000
Sent-off : Reynoso (SL), Cubilla (P)

29.05.1960 - Peñarol (Uru) 2 - San Lorenzo (Arg) 1

Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Nestor Goncalvez, Aguerre, Borges, Linazza, Alberto Spencer, Griecco, Leicht (Crescio).
San Lorenzo : Tarnawski, Paez, Iñigo, Castillo, Ferro, Martinez, Carlos Bilardo, Ruiz, O. Rossi, Jose Sanfilippo, Boggio.
Goals : Spencer -2- (P), Sanfilippo (SL)
Stadium : Centenario (Montevideo)
Referee : Jose Dimas Larrosa (Paraguay)
Attendance : 45.000
Sent-off : Griecco (P)

Qualified : PEÑAROL (URUGUAY)

 

29.05.1960 - Millonarios (Col) 0 - Olimpia (Par) 0

Millonarios : Centurion, Moyano, Zuluaga, L. Rubio, J. Ramirez Gallego, Bolla, Rodolfo Micheli, Orlando Larraz, Klinger, Alarcon, R. Pizarro.
Olimpia : Arias, Arevalo, J. Lezcano, Echague, C. Lezcano, P. Rojas, V. Rodriguez, Recalde, Doldan, P. Cabral, Osorio.
Stadium : Nemesio Camacho, "El Campin" (Bogota)
Referee : Jose Antonio Sundheim (Colombia)
Attendance : 35.000

05.06.1960 - Olimpia (Par) 5 - Millonarios (Col) 1

Olimpia : Arias, Arevalo, J. Lezcano, Osorio, C. Lezcano, P. Rojas, V. Rodriguez, Recalde, Doldan, P. Cabral, melgarejo.
Millonarios : Centurion, Moyano, Bolla, Zuluaga, J. Ramirez Gallego, R. Diaz, Larraz, R. Micheli (Noriega), Alarcon, Klinger, R. Pizarro.
Goals : Doldan -2- (O), Melgarejo (O), Recalde (O), Noriega o.g. (O), Pizarro (M).
Stadium : Manuel Ferreira (Asuncion)
Referee : Jose Luis Praddaude (Argentina)
Attendance : 35.000
Sent-off : Bolla (M)

Qualified : OLIMPIA (PARAGUAY)

 

Finals

12.06.1960 - Peñarol (Uru) 1 - Olimpia (Par) 0

Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez (Majewski), Salvador, Pino, Goncalvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Alberto Spencer, Crescio, Borges.
Olimpia : Arias, J. Lezcano, Arevalo, Rojas, C. Lezcano, Osorio, V. Rodriguez, Recalde, Doldan, P. Cabral, Melgarejo.
Goal : Spencer (P)
Stadium : Centenario (Montevideo)
Referee : Carlos Robles (Chile)
Attendance : 50.000
Sent-off : J. Lezcano (O)

19.06.1960 - Olimpia (Par) 1 - Peñarol (Uru) 1

Olimpia : Arias, Arevalo, Peralta, P. Rojas, C. Lezcano, Echague, V. Rodriguez, Recalde, Doldan, P. Cabral, Osorio.
Peñarol : Maidana, William Martinez, Salvador, Pino, Nestor Goncalvez, Aguerre, Luis Cubilla, Linazza, Alberto Spencer (Juan Hohberg), Griecco, Borges.
Goals : Recalde (O), Luis Cubilla (P)
Stadium : Manuel Ferreira (Asuncion)
Referee : Jose Luis Praddaude (Argentina)
Attendance : 20.000

CHAMPION : PEÑAROL (URUGUAY)

 

